11:05.345 --> 11:09.719
So, the good news is, Sasha Mann is

11:09.720 --> 11:11.678
- really invested in this movie.
- Mm-hmm.

11:11.679 --> 11:14.082
Are you fucking kidding me? He
gets a fucking writing credit?

11:14.083 --> 11:15.469
No, no, we...

11:15.470 --> 11:17.386
W-we can't let him have it.
We have to fight this.

11:17.387 --> 11:19.664
- We totally get how you feel.
- Hmm. Yeah.

11:19.665 --> 11:21.678
[Adam] But Hollywood's a small town.

11:21.679 --> 11:23.886
Relationships are everything.

11:23.887 --> 11:25.219
[Jordan] Think about it:

11:25.220 --> 11:26.844
"Disgruntled first-time
screenwriter battles

11:26.845 --> 11:29.490
beloved movie star in
credit arbitration."

11:29.491 --> 11:31.552
- Mm.
- Come on,

11:31.553 --> 11:32.761
- that's not a good look.
- No.

11:32.762 --> 11:34.969
I don't give a shit what it looks like.

11:34.970 --> 11:38.055
He didn't write that movie,
I fucking wrote the movie.

11:39.339 --> 11:41.344
And as my representatives,
I need you to help me

11:41.345 --> 11:42.696
stand up to him.

11:44.512 --> 11:46.569
As Sasha Mann's representatives,

11:47.064 --> 11:48.876
we're not gonna be able to do that.

11:52.764 --> 11:54.219
But wait.

11:54.220 --> 11:56.052
We have something that
will cheer you up.

11:56.053 --> 11:58.173
- Mm.
- Show him the key art, Jordan.

11:58.174 --> 12:00.303
[Jordan] We just got this.

12:03.970 --> 12:05.302
Huh?

12:05.303 --> 12:08.052
[chuckles] Come on.

12:08.053 --> 12:11.199
[chuckles] It's pretty good, right?

12:20.128 --> 12:22.461
[phone ringing]

12:24.345 --> 12:26.427
- Hey.
- [woman] Hello.

12:26.428 --> 12:28.928
- Mr. Solloway?
- Sorry, who is this?

12:28.929 --> 12:31.427
