32:06.735 --> 32:08.344
I can't.

32:08.345 --> 32:10.219
We're about to open a
new exhibition here,

32:10.220 --> 32:12.386
and I've got so much to do.

32:12.387 --> 32:13.768
Thank you, though.

32:16.301 --> 32:18.678
Okay. Well, how about I just

32:18.679 --> 32:21.552
leave this invitation here

32:21.553 --> 32:24.010
in case you can make it?

32:24.011 --> 32:25.928
Oh, look, it's a... there's a-a plus-one

32:25.929 --> 32:27.966
if you wanted to bring someone along.

32:29.173 --> 32:30.209
Look...

32:34.209 --> 32:37.167
I know we didn't part
on the best of terms.

32:37.887 --> 32:39.969
But I'm here...

32:39.970 --> 32:42.428
to try to make it up to you.

32:45.569 --> 32:47.157
Another time.

32:58.057 --> 32:59.769
This stuff is...

33:00.387 --> 33:03.260
livid with pain.

33:03.261 --> 33:05.844
[somber music]

33:05.845 --> 33:07.637
♪♪♪

33:13.595 --> 33:15.345
[door opens]

33:22.595 --> 33:23.845
[sighs]

33:34.053 --> 33:36.053
♪♪♪

33:56.637 --> 33:58.594
Hey.

33:58.595 --> 34:00.804
I was just napping.

34:03.092 --> 34:04.800
Whit, you know I don't
mind if you drink.

34:06.804 --> 34:09.135
That's okay. I'll just, um...

34:09.136 --> 34:11.761
I'll just have coffee.
That'll wake me up.

34:11.762 --> 34:14.835
Ooh... I'm sorry.

34:14.835 --> 34:16.511
- I forgot.
- Uh...

34:16.512 --> 34:18.594
- I'll go to the store.
- No, it's okay. It's okay.

34:18.594 --> 34:20.428
I just, um...

34:22.167 --> 34:24.260
I'll take a shower. That'll wake me up.

34:24.261 --> 34:25.678
Okay.

34:25.679 --> 34:27.094
[somber music]

34:27.094 --> 34:29.094
♪♪♪

34:46.512 --> 34:48.094
[typing]

34:49.344 --> 34:51.010
[inhales deeply]

34:51.011 --> 34:53.239
Oh, this book is amazing.

34:53.239 --> 34:54.764
It's an investment, but it's so worth it

34:54.766 --> 34:56.803
once you get a few hundred pages in.

34:56.804 --> 34:58.970
Must be nice to have time to read.

35:02.053 --> 35:04.068
Hey. Are you okay?

35:04.069 --> 35:05.636
Fine. I'm just tired.

35:05.637 --> 35:07.378
[typing continues]

35:07.379 --> 35:09.302
Well, why don't we call it a night?

35:09.303 --> 35:11.469
I can't. I have to finish
this fucking website.

35:11.470 --> 35:13.010
[exhales sharply]

35:13.011 --> 35:15.135
How is that your job on
top of everything else?

35:15.136 --> 35:17.094
Why can't Andrea hire
someone to do that?

35:17.463 --> 35:18.810
She's cheap as shit.

35:21.845 --> 35:24.106
God, I can't wait until we have

35:24.107 --> 35:26.006
enough money for you to quit that place.

35:27.537 --> 35:29.370
Yeah. Me, either.

35:32.424 --> 35:35.008
Are you sure everything's okay?

35:43.675 --> 35:45.260
What did you do all day?

35:45.261 --> 35:46.886
[chuckles] I worked.

35:46.887 --> 35:48.614
What does that mean?

35:48.615 --> 35:50.302
I painted, Whitney.

35:50.303 --> 35:52.206
When I came home, you were napping.

35:53.139 --> 35:54.511
Because I was tired from painting.

35:54.512 --> 35:56.895
[scoffs]

35:56.896 --> 35:58.344
Oh, that doesn't seem legitimate to you?

35:58.345 --> 36:00.302
Why can't I ever see
anything you're working on?

36:00.303 --> 36:02.345
Because it's not ready yet.

36:07.148 --> 36:09.109
Whitney, what the hell
is wrong with you?

36:10.068 --> 36:12.008
I want you to contribute here.

36:12.009 --> 36:14.346
- I want you to help me out.
- And you think I don't?

36:14.347 --> 36:16.135
I don't want to have to pay

36:16.136 --> 36:17.761
the rent by myself every month.

36:17.762 --> 36:20.257
- So let's go to city hall.
- What?

36:20.258 --> 36:22.552
Let's just go get married
at city hall tonight.

36:22.553 --> 36:25.003
- It's closed.
- Tomorrow, then.

36:25.004 --> 36:27.515
Let's go to city hall
and get it over with

36:27.516 --> 36:29.386
so I can take this idiotic test

36:29.387 --> 36:32.044
so I can work in this
godforsaken country.

36:35.622 --> 36:37.843
Why are we planning a
wedding months from now?

36:38.423 --> 36:40.010
It makes no sense.

36:40.011 --> 36:41.436
- It does to me.
- [sighs]

36:42.869 --> 36:44.770
But, I mean, come on.

36:45.704 --> 36:47.622
Let's just get married.

36:48.095 --> 36:50.219
- Don't you want to?
- Of course I want to.

36:50.220 --> 36:53.618
But I want a wedding... At
my grandparents' house.

36:54.359 --> 36:56.094
It's bad enough that we have
three months to plan it

36:56.095 --> 36:58.081
in the middle of winter; now you
don't want to do it at all?

36:58.082 --> 36:59.886
- That is not what I said.
- Now you just want to get it over with?

36:59.887 --> 37:01.016
- That's not what I said.
- Yes, it is!

37:01.017 --> 37:02.177
That is what you said.

37:02.178 --> 37:04.220
[sighs]

37:10.303 --> 37:12.136
[sighs]

37:12.137 --> 37:13.917
It was just a thought.

37:13.918 --> 37:15.092
[sighs]

37:15.093 --> 37:16.605
Please come back to bed.

37:29.387 --> 37:31.803
[somber music]

37:31.804 --> 37:33.845
♪♪♪

37:50.679 --> 37:52.470
♪♪♪

38:12.679 --> 38:16.169
We should probably practice
some more interview questions.

38:16.170 --> 38:18.130
Okay.

38:21.635 --> 38:23.584
What's my favorite color?

38:24.303 --> 38:25.916
Cobalt blue.

38:28.782 --> 38:30.678
How many cousins do I have?

38:30.679 --> 38:32.303
Thirteen.

38:34.124 --> 38:35.795
Where did we meet?

38:36.470 --> 38:38.006
Spring Fling.

38:41.512 --> 38:43.512
♪♪♪

38:51.679 --> 38:53.470
[sighs]

39:07.637 --> 39:09.387
[sighs]

39:13.637 --> 39:15.344
Whose house is this?

39:15.345 --> 39:16.969
Carolina Wineman.

39:16.970 --> 39:19.094
Her husband's a director, Barry?

39:19.095 --> 39:20.552
This is Barry Wineman's house?

39:20.553 --> 39:21.886
- Yep.
- Jesus, Mom.

39:21.887 --> 39:23.879
- How did this happen?
- Nepotism.

39:24.780 --> 39:26.719
I-I guess Barry hasn't had a hit movie

39:26.720 --> 39:28.636
in a while, so Sasha's
doing his new one,

39:28.637 --> 39:30.720
so Barry owes Sasha a favor, so...

39:32.762 --> 39:35.855
I'm trying to start a new
career later in life.

39:35.856 --> 39:37.358
I will take all the help I can get.

39:37.359 --> 39:40.113
What should I do with these... walls?

39:40.114 --> 39:41.480
What's her budget?

39:41.481 --> 39:42.636
She doesn't seem to have one.

39:42.637 --> 39:45.469
Huh. Um...

39:45.470 --> 39:49.552
Maybe a big Harold
Ancart mixed media here?

39:50.554 --> 39:52.683
Maybe a Joyce Pensato charcoal there,

39:52.684 --> 39:54.003
a Kerry James Marshall here.

39:54.004 --> 39:56.260
I think I can get her a
discount through the gallery.

39:56.261 --> 39:57.914
Andrea's brother represents her.

40:00.679 --> 40:02.469
What?

40:02.470 --> 40:05.129
I don't know. I'm just so proud of you.

40:07.637 --> 40:09.981
- You are?
- Yeah. I mean, look at you.

40:09.982 --> 40:12.287
24 years old, and you're so successful.

40:12.967 --> 40:15.427
- Not exactly.
- Well, yeah.

40:15.428 --> 40:19.052
Do you know what I was
doing when I was 24?

40:19.053 --> 40:21.469
- What?
- Well...

40:21.470 --> 40:25.552
I had followed your father to Europe,

40:25.553 --> 40:27.856
and I was working...

40:28.889 --> 40:32.219
in a bagel factory to support
us while he wrote his "memoir."

40:32.220 --> 40:33.637
Hey, Mom, it's 10 a.m.

40:36.512 --> 40:38.636
[glasses clink]

40:38.637 --> 40:41.094
Wow, so a bagel factory.
You never told me that.

40:41.095 --> 40:42.803
[chuckles] Yeah.

40:42.804 --> 40:46.052
I think I probably
tried to block it out.

40:46.053 --> 40:47.469
For how long?

40:47.470 --> 40:49.469
- Um... I don't know.
- [opener whirring]

40:49.470 --> 40:51.594
- [whirring stops]
- A long time.

40:51.595 --> 40:53.386
A year, I think?

40:53.387 --> 40:54.804
- [whirring resumes]
- I hated it.

40:56.512 --> 40:58.302
- [corks pops]
- Why didn't you leave?

40:58.303 --> 41:00.469
[sighs] I was probably...

41:00.470 --> 41:02.552
I don't know, afraid of...

41:02.553 --> 41:04.053
disappointing your father?

41:06.387 --> 41:08.177
I really wish I hadn't
spent so much time

41:08.178 --> 41:09.427
doing that when I was younger.

41:09.428 --> 41:11.136
I could have accomplished so much more.

41:20.115 --> 41:21.357
Hey, Mom?

41:22.285 --> 41:23.886
How are you doing financially?

41:23.887 --> 41:26.281
Oh, God, I'm in a fucking hole.

41:26.282 --> 41:28.808
I mean, I don't... that's...
I need this job to go well.

41:28.809 --> 41:30.636
Or I'm afraid I'm gonna
have to sell the house.

41:30.637 --> 41:32.678
Or pull your brother and
sister out of school.

41:32.679 --> 41:33.888
Or both.

41:35.553 --> 41:36.961
Why? How are you?

41:38.201 --> 41:39.472
We're fine.

41:41.929 --> 41:44.235
Hi. I'm so sorry I'm late.

41:44.236 --> 41:46.094
Traffic was insane.

41:46.095 --> 41:47.344
Honey.

41:47.345 --> 41:49.386
How could you not have
told me that you know

41:49.387 --> 41:51.111
the vagina man, never mind dated him?

41:51.112 --> 41:52.723
Oh, well...

41:52.724 --> 41:54.260
it really didn't end well, so I...

41:54.261 --> 41:57.463
Well, I'm sorry, men are dogs.
But I am absolutely thrilled

41:57.464 --> 42:00.229
that we are still invited to his
opening at The Broad tonight.

42:00.230 --> 42:02.427
You know what? I actually
lost the invitation.

42:02.428 --> 42:04.511
I'm really sorry. Security's so tight

42:04.512 --> 42:06.553
- at events like that.
- Oh, and I found it.

42:09.099 --> 42:11.427
Look, Andrea, I-I just don't think

42:11.428 --> 42:13.552
that my fiancé would appreciate me going

42:13.553 --> 42:15.813
to an event like this
with my ex-boyfriend.

42:16.368 --> 42:18.177
That is so sweet.

42:18.694 --> 42:20.010
But it's irrelevant.

42:20.011 --> 42:23.469
What I'm getting at...
is that you are going

42:23.470 --> 42:25.777
to this opening at The Broad tonight.

42:26.637 --> 42:29.530
Because I... am going.

42:39.804 --> 42:41.595
[footsteps approaching]

42:44.780 --> 42:46.154
What?

42:46.155 --> 42:47.781
I didn't say anything.

42:54.259 --> 42:55.761
How do I look?

42:55.762 --> 42:57.392
[sniffles]

42:57.393 --> 42:58.812
Like someone else.

43:00.424 --> 43:02.719
Good. That's the point.

43:03.311 --> 43:04.890
Where you going?

43:04.891 --> 43:07.219
There's an opening at The Broad tonight.

43:07.220 --> 43:09.105
Oh, wow, The Broad.

43:09.939 --> 43:11.636
That monument to postwar capitalism

43:11.637 --> 43:13.636
masquerading as accessible art.

43:13.637 --> 43:16.469
I'm sorry, but Basquiat is at The Broad.

43:16.470 --> 43:19.135
Ed Ruscha, Jasper Johns.
How can you possibly

43:19.136 --> 43:21.135
look down on an institution like that?

43:21.136 --> 43:23.355
Because it's not really a museum.

43:23.356 --> 43:25.193
It's a glorified, Instagrammable

43:25.194 --> 43:27.263
storage locker for money and ego.

43:30.675 --> 43:32.306
You don't have to come.

43:33.580 --> 43:35.330
I wasn't invited.

43:36.696 --> 43:38.232
[sighs]

43:39.303 --> 43:41.135
Whose opening are you even going to?

43:41.136 --> 43:43.427
Photographer named Furkat.

43:43.428 --> 43:46.219
That guy? Are you kidding?

43:46.220 --> 43:49.175
That man should be in prison,
not a museum. He's a pedophile.

43:49.176 --> 43:50.969
[scoffs] You know, as much as I'd love

43:50.970 --> 43:52.803
to stick around for another lecture

43:52.804 --> 43:56.435
about the moral bankruptcy of
modern Neo-Pop, I have to go.

43:56.436 --> 43:57.757
You don't have to do anything.

43:57.758 --> 43:59.803
Actually, Colin, I do.

43:59.804 --> 44:01.719
I have to make a living,
and sometimes that means

44:01.720 --> 44:03.177
interacting with people
who don't live up

44:03.178 --> 44:05.219
to your impossible standard
of artistic integrity.

44:05.220 --> 44:06.636
You like it.

44:06.637 --> 44:07.761
What?

44:07.762 --> 44:09.511
Admit it, you like it.

44:09.512 --> 44:10.756
You like getting dressed up

44:10.757 --> 44:12.692
and hanging out with the popular crowd.

44:13.885 --> 44:15.511
You think it makes you cool.

44:18.462 --> 44:20.391
You really can be such a dick.

44:26.095 --> 44:28.219
[lively chatter]

44:28.220 --> 44:29.719
[dance music playing]

44:29.720 --> 44:33.000
Oh, my God. Everybody's here.

44:33.001 --> 44:35.928
Um, if people ask if we're
sisters, just say yes, right?

44:35.929 --> 44:37.844
- [chuckles]
- I mean, wouldn't that be fun?

44:37.845 --> 44:39.302
- Sure, Andrea.
- Okay.

44:39.303 --> 44:40.679
Whatever you want.

44:53.413 --> 44:55.409
[clicks tongue]

44:55.410 --> 44:57.117
Here she is.

44:58.053 --> 44:59.887
Whitney Solloway.

45:01.220 --> 45:02.917
The one that got away.

45:02.918 --> 45:04.552
Oh, uh, my love,

45:04.553 --> 45:08.474
I must introduce you to
a dear friend of mine.

45:08.475 --> 45:10.177
Dashiell?

45:10.178 --> 45:12.344
Oh.

45:12.345 --> 45:15.587
- Dashiell Boucicault.
- Hi.

45:15.588 --> 45:17.442
Ah. Lindsay's mentioned you.

45:17.443 --> 45:19.042
Lindsay?

45:19.043 --> 45:22.719
Thanks. It's the name my mama gave me.

45:22.720 --> 45:24.886
- [chuckles]
- Andrea Rossman.

45:24.887 --> 45:26.928
Whitney is my gallery assistant.

45:26.929 --> 45:28.636
Oh. Hello.

45:28.637 --> 45:31.667
[Andrea] I, uh, have been
a fan of yours for years.

45:31.668 --> 45:33.426
I would love to pick your brain

45:33.427 --> 45:34.886
about the collection that you've built.

45:34.887 --> 45:36.745
Have you seen the Therrien?

45:36.746 --> 45:39.186
It will make you feel so small.

45:41.204 --> 45:45.511
He's a very important collector.

45:45.512 --> 45:48.037
- Do you know him?
- No.

45:48.845 --> 45:51.122
Uh, he's opening a new
gallery in New York.

45:51.804 --> 45:55.096
I'm hoping to be his inaugural artist.

45:55.097 --> 45:57.046
I'm sure you will be.

45:58.156 --> 46:00.094
He'll need an assistant.

46:00.095 --> 46:01.886
And you could use an upgrade.

46:01.887 --> 46:04.220
Yeah. I'm fine where I am.

46:07.512 --> 46:10.344
Darling, um, come with me.

46:10.345 --> 46:12.469
I need to talk to you.

46:12.470 --> 46:14.302
I think I should go rescue your friend

46:14.303 --> 46:15.515
- from Andrea.
- Listen, I...

46:16.591 --> 46:18.384
I have to show you something.

46:19.510 --> 46:21.469
The last time we went somewhere to talk,

46:21.470 --> 46:23.389
it didn't go so well.

46:25.261 --> 46:28.511
I think we've both come a long way

46:28.512 --> 46:30.969
from Paris.

46:30.970 --> 46:32.970
Haven't we?

46:35.595 --> 46:37.136
Come on.

46:39.887 --> 46:41.969
[soft music playing]

46:41.970 --> 46:43.970
♪♪♪

46:51.196 --> 46:53.763
So, are you gonna apologize now or what?

46:58.178 --> 46:59.679
[sighs]

47:04.582 --> 47:06.177
I'm sorry.

47:06.178 --> 47:08.852
I'm so sorry, Whitney.

47:08.853 --> 47:11.245
I was an ass.

47:13.115 --> 47:14.844
There's not a... a day goes by

47:14.845 --> 47:19.420
where I don't regret
what happened in Paris.

47:20.720 --> 47:23.483
That I could do that to any woman,

47:23.484 --> 47:25.916
but to you,

47:26.929 --> 47:31.849
the perfect... perfect woman.

47:34.765 --> 47:35.973
I'm sorry.

47:37.966 --> 47:39.633
Will you forgive me?

47:41.980 --> 47:45.090
Please, please forgive me.

47:46.066 --> 47:47.648
[quietly] Furkat.

47:47.649 --> 47:49.094
Stop. Get up.

47:49.095 --> 47:51.937
- You're embarrassing me.
- Not until you forgive me.

47:51.938 --> 47:54.177
Oh, my God, stop it. You're... Stand up.

47:54.178 --> 47:55.511
Not until you forgive me!

47:55.512 --> 47:57.720
What...?

47:59.053 --> 48:01.052
[dramatic music]

48:01.053 --> 48:03.053
♪♪♪

48:22.802 --> 48:24.051
What is happening?

48:24.052 --> 48:26.929
It's all for you.

48:28.095 --> 48:29.886
Furkat, please, just stand up.

48:29.887 --> 48:31.594
- Do you forgive me?
- Yes.

48:31.595 --> 48:33.552
- No, you don't.
- Please, Furkat,

48:33.553 --> 48:35.219
- just stand up.
- Say it.

48:35.220 --> 48:37.094
- Say what?
- Say you forgive me.

48:37.095 --> 48:39.010
I do. I forgive you. Just get up!

48:39.011 --> 48:41.261
I forgive you, I forgive
you, I forgive you.

48:43.887 --> 48:47.011
[applause, cheering]

48:54.512 --> 48:56.553
♪♪♪

49:02.387 --> 49:04.428
Stop. Stop.

49:07.387 --> 49:09.177
[dance music pulsing]

49:09.178 --> 49:11.220
♪♪♪

49:13.720 --> 49:17.229
[grunts, exhales]

49:17.230 --> 49:20.678
So, how long have you
known F... Lindsay?

49:20.679 --> 49:22.010
[chuckles]

49:22.011 --> 49:25.136
Uh, we met a few months ago at Basel.

49:26.637 --> 49:29.511
He's very talented.

49:29.512 --> 49:31.302
That's funny.

49:31.303 --> 49:33.427
He says the same thing about you.

49:33.428 --> 49:35.010
He does?

49:35.011 --> 49:37.094
Mm-hmm.

49:37.095 --> 49:39.679
He said that you have an amazing eye.

49:45.178 --> 49:47.719
[laughter, indistinct chatter nearby]

49:47.720 --> 49:49.485
They are so beautiful.

49:56.587 --> 49:58.462
Yeah, I was just thinking that.

50:00.187 --> 50:01.511
You should join them.

50:01.512 --> 50:03.261
[chuckles]

50:06.317 --> 50:07.734
Prefer to watch?

50:10.470 --> 50:12.428
Yeah, me, too.

50:15.178 --> 50:19.260
You know, I used to want
to model for Lindsay,

50:19.261 --> 50:20.636
when I was younger.

50:20.637 --> 50:22.928
[laughs]

50:22.929 --> 50:24.469
When you were younger.

50:24.470 --> 50:26.969
- Well, I meant...
- Yeah.

50:27.844 --> 50:29.720
I know what you meant.

50:31.011 --> 50:32.636
[drink pouring]

50:33.255 --> 50:34.663
And now?

50:35.696 --> 50:37.928
I don't want to be looked at anymore.

50:37.929 --> 50:40.178
I want to be the one
that does the looking.

50:40.179 --> 50:42.803
Well, that is where all the power lies.

50:42.804 --> 50:44.512
[laughs softly]

50:47.175 --> 50:49.547
If you could have everything you wanted,

50:50.804 --> 50:52.210
what would it look like?

50:57.541 --> 50:59.096
Well...

51:01.428 --> 51:03.010
Somebody would give me the money

51:03.011 --> 51:06.313
to start my own gallery where I could

51:08.716 --> 51:10.552
foster new artists.

51:10.553 --> 51:12.386
Younger artists.

51:12.387 --> 51:16.969
So much of what I see now
feels recycled, redundant...

51:16.970 --> 51:19.094
built for an audience
that already exists

51:19.095 --> 51:21.453
as opposed to in search of a new one.

51:22.387 --> 51:26.142
I'd want to promote artists
that are digging deeper,

51:26.143 --> 51:27.662
that are looking for something amorphous

51:27.663 --> 51:29.676
that haunts them, that haunts me,

51:29.677 --> 51:31.427
that I just don't have the language for.

51:31.428 --> 51:32.776
[laughs softly]

51:34.553 --> 51:36.511
